  "title": "GUI Chat Protocol — From Text Chat to Multi-Modal AI",
  "description": "An overview of the GUI Chat Protocol: how a simple enhancement to standard tool calling brings rich GUI and multi-modal interaction to LLM chat, enables code-free composable roles, and points toward a chat-centric operating system.",
  "lang": "en",
  "beats": [
    {
      "text": "GUI Chat Protocol: a natural extension of tool calling that brings graphical, multi-modal interaction to LLM chat interfaces.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "title",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Protocol Overview"
          },
          "titleSize": "hero",
          "subtitleSize": "lead",
          "title": "GUI Chat Protocol",
          "subtitle": "From text-only chat to {primary:rich, interactive, multi-modal AI}",
          "chips": [
            "🔧 built on tool calling",
            "🖼️ typed GUI results",
            "🔁 bidirectional",
            "🧩 model-agnostic"
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Conversational AI has been trapped in a text-only paradigm — but many real-world use cases need visual and interactive elements.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "comparison",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Motivation"
          },
          "title": "Text alone isn't enough",
          "left": {
            "title": "Text-Only Chat",
            "accentColor": "danger",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  {
                    "text": "User sends text, LLM responds with text",
                    "icon": "no"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "Linear interaction, no visual context",
                    "icon": "no"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "Rich content described, never shown",
                    "icon": "warn"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          "right": {
            "title": "What Users Actually Need",
            "accentColor": "success",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  {
                    "text": "Generated images & edited photos",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "Maps, charts, data visualizations",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "Games, quizzes, media players",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          "callout": {
            "text": "Leverage {primary:existing tool calling infrastructure} to trigger GUI components — no new architecture.",
            "label": "Key idea",
            "color": "info",
            "leftBar": true
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "From the LLM's perspective, nothing changes — it's standard function calling. The enhancement lives in the tool result.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "columns",
          "accentColor": "primary",
          "title": "It's just a tool call",
          "stepLabel": "CORE CONCEPT",
          "subtitle": "The LLM never needs to know it's driving a GUI",
          "columns": [
            {
              "title": "LLM calls tool",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Standard function calling with JSON arguments."
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "Tool defs in system prompt",
                    "Standard JSON Schema",
                    "No special model capability"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "num": 1
            },
            {
              "title": "Tool returns twice",
              "accentColor": "accent",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "One result, two payloads."
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "`message` + `jsonData` → LLM",
                    "typed `data` → the UI",
                    "optional `instructions` guide follow-up"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "num": 2
            },
            {
              "title": "UI renders type",
              "accentColor": "success",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "The `type` tag picks the visual component."
                },
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "Full-size view in canvas",
                    "Compact preview in sidebar",
                    "Conversation continues normally"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "num": 3
            }
          ],
          "showArrows": true
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Each typed payload maps to a registered component — image viewers, maps, games, music players, forms, and more.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "grid",
          "accentColor": "accent",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Typed Return Data"
          },
          "title": "Types drive the rendering",
          "subtitle": "Every type pairs a full-size view with a sidebar preview",
          "gridColumns": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "image",
              "description": "Image viewer for generated or edited pictures",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "icon": "🖼️"
            },
            {
              "title": "map",
              "description": "Interactive map with markers and zoom",
              "accentColor": "info",
              "icon": "🗺️"
            },
            {
              "title": "game",
              "description": "Game boards — Othello, Go, quizzes",
              "accentColor": "accent",
              "icon": "🎮"
            },
            {
              "title": "music",
              "description": "Music and podcast players",
              "accentColor": "highlight",
              "icon": "🎵"
            },
            {
              "title": "browse",
              "description": "Web content viewer",
              "accentColor": "success",
              "icon": "🌐"
            },
            {
              "title": "form",
              "description": "Structured input collection",
              "accentColor": "warning",
              "icon": "📝"
            },
            {
              "title": "document",
              "description": "Rich markdown with embedded images",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "icon": "📄"
            },
            {
              "title": "…extensible",
              "description": "Register new types without touching chat logic",
              "accentColor": "info",
              "icon": "➕"
            }
          ],
          "footer": "Existing text tools keep working unchanged — adoption is incremental."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "The protocol isn't just output — GUI forms collect structured input and send it back to the LLM as JSON.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "split",
          "accentColor": "primary",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Bidirectional"
          },
          "left": {
            "title": "The round trip",
            "label": "FLOW",
            "accentColor": "primary",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "GUI components both **present to** and **collect from** users.",
                "bold": true
              },
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  "LLM calls `presentForm` with field defs",
                  "User fills the form in the GUI",
                  "Submission returns as a JSON text message",
                  "LLM parses it and responds — e.g. a recipe document"
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "callout",
                "text": "Enables guided tutorials, form-based workflows, and interactive apps.",
                "style": "info"
              }
            ],
            "ratio": 50
          },
          "right": {
            "title": "Form submission → LLM",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "code",
                "code": "{\n  \"formSubmission\": {\n    \"formTitle\": \"Recipe Preferences\",\n    \"responses\": {\n      \"dish\": \"Spaghetti Carbonara\",\n      \"servings\": 4,\n      \"skillLevel\": \"Intermediate\",\n      \"time\": \"1 hour\",\n      \"dietary\": \"No dairy\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
              }
            ],
            "dark": true,
            "ratio": 50
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Because it builds on standard function calling, the protocol works with any capable model — OpenAI, Claude, Gemini, or open-weight models.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "grid",
          "accentColor": "info",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "LLM Agnostic"
          },
          "title": "Works with any model",
          "subtitle": "No special capabilities beyond basic function calling",
          "gridColumns": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "OpenAI GPT",
              "description": "Native function calling",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "icon": "🤖"
            },
            {
              "title": "Anthropic Claude",
              "description": "Tool use feature",
              "accentColor": "accent",
              "icon": "🧠"
            },
            {
              "title": "Google Gemini",
              "description": "Function declarations",
              "accentColor": "info",
              "icon": "✨"
            },
            {
              "title": "Open weights",
              "description": "Llama, Mistral, and beyond",
              "accentColor": "success",
              "icon": "🔓"
            }
          ],
          "footer": "Standard JSON Schema definitions · standard invocation patterns · structured JSON results"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "The most powerful idea: complete AI applications defined with zero custom code. A role is just tools plus a system prompt.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "manifesto",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Composable Roles",
            "color": "warning"
          },
          "title": "The role {primary:IS} the application",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Tools + prompt. That's it.",
              "description": "A role is a tool selection plus a system prompt — no code, no components, no custom logic.",
              "accentColor": "primary"
            },
            {
              "title": "The chat app stays generic.",
              "description": "It only executes tools, renders typed data, and relays user input. All specifics live in the role.",
              "accentColor": "accent"
            },
            {
              "title": "Prototype in minutes.",
              "description": "Recipe Guide, Trip Planner, Tutor, Game Companion — each is just a different configuration.",
              "accentColor": "success"
            },
            {
              "title": "Anyone can build one.",
              "description": "Non-programmers create specialized AI assistants by editing text, not shipping code.",
              "accentColor": "warning"
            }
          ],
          "columns": 2
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "For example, a Recipe Guide role composes six existing tools with a short behavioral prompt.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "split",
          "accentColor": "success",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Example Role"
          },
          "left": {
            "title": "Available tools",
            "label": "COMPOSE",
            "accentColor": "success",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  "presentForm — collect preferences",
                  "presentDocument — recipe w/ images",
                  "generateImage — step-by-step visuals",
                  "browse + searchWeb — look up recipes",
                  "scrollToAnchor — hands-free navigation"
                ]
              }
            ],
            "ratio": 45
          },
          "right": {
            "title": "System prompt (the behavior)",
            "accentColor": "primary",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  {
                    "text": "**Greet** the user warmly",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "**Collect** dish, servings, skill, time via form",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "**Create** recipe document with embedded images",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "**Assist hands-free** — scroll to a step, read it aloud",
                    "icon": "ok"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "callout",
                "text": "Same pattern yields Trip Planner, Clinic Receptionist, Tutor, Weather Reporter, Game Companion…",
                "style": "info"
              }
            ],
            "ratio": 55
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Because roles are pure data, the LLM can switch between them dynamically — or even create new ones on the fly.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "timeline",
          "accentColor": "accent",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Meta-Capabilities"
          },
          "title": "Roles are data — so they're dynamic",
          "subtitle": "From switching to self-evolution",
          "items": [
            {
              "date": "switchRole()",
              "title": "Dynamic switching",
              "description": "LLM or user changes role\nmid-conversation",
              "color": "primary",
              "done": true
            },
            {
              "date": "createRole()",
              "title": "On-the-fly creation",
              "description": "LLM designs a custom role\nfrom a user's description",
              "color": "accent",
              "hot": true
            },
            {
              "date": "Marketplace",
              "title": "Shared roles",
              "description": "Community-created roles,\ndownloadable & remixable",
              "color": "info"
            },
            {
              "date": "Self-evolving",
              "title": "Adaptive apps",
              "description": "Roles refine themselves\nfrom user feedback",
              "color": "success"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "The long-term vision: conversation replaces applications as the primary interface of the operating system.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "table",
          "accentColor": "primary",
          "eyebrow": {
            "label": "Future Direction",
            "color": "highlight"
          },
          "title": "Toward a chat-centric OS",
          "subtitle": "The paradigm shift, dimension by dimension",
          "headers": [
            "Dimension",
            "App-Centric OS",
            "Chat-Centric OS"
          ],
          "rows": [
            [
              "Primary interface",
